The trap density of the film is measured with the space-charge-limited current analysis under different biases to characterize the crystallinity of MAPbBr3 SC-TF quantitatively. For the electrical characterization, Au electrodes are thermally deposited on both top and bottom surfaces of the free-standing film. As shown in Fig. 3f, the I-V characteristics of the film changes at VTFL = 0.008 V. Below 0.008 V, the I-V curve shows an Ohmic contact characteristic. Above 0.008 V, the current rises sharply with voltage, resulted from all trap states being filled by injected charge carriers. The trap density is gotten from ntrap=2εrε0VTFLed2=1.6×1011cm-3\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
